[3] China (Chongqing): imported case, details
Source: Caixin Global [edited]
https://www.caixinglobal.com/2022-09-21/chongqing-monkeypox-patient-caught-the-disease-in-berlin-china-cdc-says-101942916.html


The Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) has disclosed details of the mainland's 1st monkeypox case, saying the patient was a 29-year-old salesman who had recently visited Germany, where he had sex with men.

The man said he had sexual contact with men in Berlin on 2 Sep 2022, according to a weekly report published by the China CDC on Monday [19 Sep 2022]. He subsequently traveled to Spain and developed symptoms including an itchy throat, fever, and rashes. On 14 Sep 2022, he returned to the southwestern Chinese municipality of Chongqing and was isolated in a local COVID-19 quarantine facility, according to the report.

Gene sequencing suggests that the virus strain of the imported case, which was confirmed in Chongqing on Friday [16 Sep 2022], belongs to the B.1 branch of the West African lineage of the disease, and is "highly" similar to strains from Germany collected on 21 Jun [2022], the report said.

