[4] Sudan: 5 new cases
Date: Tue 20 Sep 2022 1:55 PM EET
Source: Journal-Courier, Associated Press (AP) report [abridged, edited]
https://www.myjournalcourier.com/news/article/Sudan-detects-5-more-cases-of-monkeypox-amid-17454703.php


Sudan on Tuesday [20 Sep 2022] announced 5 more cases of the monkeypox virus, bringing the tally up to 7 patients.

The Health Ministry said in a statement the new cases were detected in the capital of Khartoum and the provinces of West Darfur, North Darfur, and Kassala. The statement did not provide further details.

Of the 7 cases, 4 were detected so far in the county were in West Darfur, including the 1st patient of the virus.

Sudan's healthcare system has been the victim of long-running domestic conflicts and recent political upheaval, as well as international isolation. It would be hard pressed to handle a large outbreak of the new disease.

